<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1904-02-12T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1904-02-12T00:00:00-05:00" n="37" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d37">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Storer</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Hay</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Vienna</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1904-02-12"><hi rend="italic">February 12,
                                    1904</hi></date></dateline></opener>
                        <p>(Mr. Storer states that the Austrian Government is disposed in a general
                            way to follow any concurrent use of good offices neutral powers having
                            more important interests involved than those of Austria may agree upon,
                            but wishes to be informed beforehand, if possible, of the extent of
                            territory on which the neutrality of China is to be respected, and asks
                            whether it is desired to include Manchuria.)</p>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>